replies.bodyText:
I agree and disagree.
Agree: I would iterate over problems and log each of them as a separate line.
Disagree: I think the method works fine as it is, right now we don't unit test it directly, but it could be directly unit tested, and it's a richer interface to have it return a problems array instead of a boolean. What I would add is an overload:
 private static List<String> verify(ConfigValue expectedRoot, ConfigValue actualRoot) {
    ArrayList<String> problems = new ArrayList<>();
    verify("", expectedConfig.root(), unifiedConfig.root(), problems);
    return problems;
}

IMHO it's nice to add an overload in such cases to make the calling code more oblivious to the internal details of the recursive method.

